@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>


<div class="privacey-1">
    <div class="home-page-2"></div>
    <div class="group-757-3">
        <div class="group-692-4">
            <p class="text-5"><span class="text-rgb-255-211-126">Privacy Policy</span></p>
            <div class="frame-13-6">
                <div class="arrow-right-7">
                    <img src="~/images/icon-8.svg" class="icon-8" alt="icon" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-9">
        <span class="text-white">
            1. Introduction
            At PayMaster, we value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data. This policy explains what information we collect, why we collect it, and how we keep it secure.
            By using PayMaster (web or mobile app), you agree to this Privacy Policy.

            2. Information We Collect
            We may collect and process the following information:
            - Employee data: name, job title, department, basic salary, attendance records, performance evaluations.
            - Work-related data: working hours, leave requests, overtime details.
            - Financial data: bonuses, deductions, and salary payments.
            - Account data: email, username, and authentication details.
            - Technical data: device type, IP address, login history (for security purposes).

            3. How We Use Your Data
            We use your information to:
            - Calculate salaries, bonuses, and deductions automatically.
            - Generate accurate reports for employees and management.
            - Provide real-time notifications (salary credited, leave approved, performance updates).
            - Improve system accuracy and efficiency.
            - Ensure compliance with company and legal regulations.

            4. Data Protection &amp; Security
            - All sensitive data is encrypted during transmission and storage.
            - Access to data is restricted by Role-Based Access Control (Admin, Supervisor, Employee).
            - We regularly update and monitor our systems to prevent unauthorized access.
            - Backups are maintained to prevent data loss.

            5. Data Sharing
            - We do not sell or rent your data to third parties.
            - Data may be shared only with authorized company administrators or as required by law.
            - Third-party integrations (e.g., attendance systems, payment providers) are used only for payroll purposes and comply with privacy standards.

            6. User Rights
            You have the right to:
            - Access your personal data.
            - Request corrections to inaccurate data.
            - Request deletion of your data (subject to legal and company requirements).
            - Limit or object to certain processing activities.

            7. Retention Policy
            We retain employee data only as long as necessary for payroll and legal compliance. Once no longer required, data is securely deleted.

            8. Updates to This Policy
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be communicated through the platform.

            9. Contact Us
            If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or how your data is handled, please contact us at:
            📧
        </span>
    </p>
    <div class="frame-2-10"></div>
</div>